7.11	Sellmeier_equation	Sellmeier equation	The Sellmeier equation is an empirical relationship between refractive index and wavelength for a particular transparent medium. The equation is used to determine the dispersion of light in the medium.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4f/Sellmeier-equation.svg/220px-Sellmeier-equation.svg.png
